<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06011252 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06011252 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  JUVENILE; MEN; ARREST; AUTO; ROBBERY; GILROY  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Two 14-year-old boys accused of fleeing from police in stolen cars are incustody today after just about everything  went wrong.;    California HighwayPatrol officers in Gilroy first noticed the boys driving north on Highway 101in separate cars about 2:10 a.m. today. One appeared to be driving under theinfluence of drugs or alcohol, said CHP Officer Ron Chaffee.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  TWO TEENS IN CUSTODY AFTER STOLEN-CAR CHASE  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     When an officer tried to stop the car, a Pontiac TransAm, the seconddriver, in a Chevrolet Caprice, attempted to run the patrol car off the road,he said.;    The TransAm made a U-turn and headed back toward Gilroy, whilethe Caprice went north with two patrol cars in pursuit. They followed theCaprice to San Leandro, at speeds up to 110 mph, Chaffee said.;    At SanLeandro, the Caprice ran out of gas, and the driver was taken into custody onsuspicion of 16 counts of assault with a deadly weapon -- the car. The driveralso was arrested on suspicion of stealing the Caprice, evading arrest andvarious other traffic violations, Chaffee said.;    Meanwhile, the driver ofthe TransAm stopped the car at a CHP weighing station north of Gilroy, hoppeda fence and took off across a field, losing the officers following him.;   About an hour and a half later, dispatchers received a call  from a highwaycall box. The caller wanted to be connected with his grandfather so he couldget a ride home, Chaffee said.;    The dispatcher was suspicious and sent apolice unit instead. Officers found the 14-year-old driver of the TransAm andbooked him for investigation of car theft, failure to yield and other trafficviolations.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  JOANNE GRANT, Mercury News Staff Writer  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910111  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  January  </MONTH><PG.COL>  6B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  277  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday, January 11, 199100011252,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>